{
  "texts": [
    "Comprehensively demonstrated the gender, racial, and Western biases that exist in the COCO [47] dataset.",
    "The research finds lighter-skinned individuals are 7.5× more common than darker-skinned individuals, and males are 2× more common than females.",
    "This leads to the concern that image captioning models may come to see the world as being predominantly occupied by lightskinned males.",
    "Worryingly, [75] also find the existence of racial slurs in the ground truth captions which leads to concerns about captioning models producing captions containing this derogatory language.Hirota et al. [76] continue the work of [75] but focus on VQA datasets.",
    "They find evidence of bias in Visual Genome [46] and OK-VQA [51], two widely used VQA datasets."
  ]
}